             was indicted for <rs id="t18280911-277-off1420" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-off1420" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-off1420" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-277-cd1421" type="crimeDate">20th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-277-off1420 t18280911-277-cd1421"></join>, 1 truck, value 3l.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18280911-277-victim1534" type="victimName">
                  Jacob 
                  Spurgen
               <interp inst="t18280911-277-victim1534" type="surname" value="Spurgen"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-victim1534" type="given" value="Jacob"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-victim1534" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-277-off1420 t18280911-277-victim1534"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JACOB SPURGEN. I am a <rs id="t18280911-277-viclabel1422" type="occupation">wheelwright</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-277-victim1534 t18280911-277-viclabel1422"></join>, and live <placeName id="t18280911-277-crimeloc1423">in Bullyard, Gray's Inn-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-277-crimeloc1423" type="placeName" value="in Bullyard, Gray's Inn-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-277-crimeloc1423" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-277-off1420 t18280911-277-crimeloc1423"></join>. On Wednesday, the 20th of August, the prisoner came to hire my truck; I refused it to him, and some time after I missed it - I saw him on the Friday; I asked him when the truck was coming home; he said that night, but it did not come - on the Saturday I saw him; he said he had taken it home, but I took him - it had not been returned; when I asked him for it, he d-d, and said I might get it as I could.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I had hired the truck before. Witness. No- he never hired it in his life; I believe he had worked for me part of a day - I do not know when.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-277-person1535">
                  THOMAS 
                  McGRATH
               <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1535" type="surname" value="McGRATH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1535" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1535" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a watchman. I took charge of the prisoner on the 23d of August.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110149"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-277-person1536">
                  GEORGE 
                  FERGUSON
               <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1536" type="surname" value="FERGUSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1536" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1536" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner that Wednesday night, in a house, in Bunhill-row; he said he had a truck for sale, and asked where he could sell it - I declined to do anything with it; and next morning I saw him going down Holborn with a truck; he spoke to me - I returned in an hour and a half, and he then took the truck and went away.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. What time were you in the Borough with me? A. I went to the Borough with him I think four weeks ago last Wednesday; he said it was on business for his master.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-277-person1537">
                  JOHN 
                  LEADBITTER
               <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1537" type="surname" value="LEADBITTER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1537" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1537" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live near the prosecutor's shop. I saw the prisoner there on the 20th of August; he looked at the shop, went in and came out; went in again, and took the board of the truck into the shop - he then went and took the truck out of the yard.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Have you not seen me before? A. Yes - I have seen you in Gray's Inn-lane; I never saw you in the house, nor the shop - I have seen him in the yard, and in the Bull public-house: I have to mind the shop while the men go to dinner - it was at dinner time I saw him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. In the deposition it was stated that I had hired the truck and was to pay 6s., and I did not return it; I had worked for him and hired the truck.</p>
               <p>COURT to the PROSECUTOR. Q. Have you seen the truck. A. No, and when I asked the prisoner for it, he d-d me, and said I might get it as I could.</p>
               <p>COURT to 
               <persName id="t18280911-277-person1538">
                  THOMAS 
                  McGRATH
               <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1538" type="surname" value="McGRATH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1538" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-person1538" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Q. Did the prisoner say anything about the truck? A. No - Mr. Spurgen said if he would bring it home he would forgive him the hire of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-277-verdict1424" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-277-verdict1424" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 48.</p>
